... am I looking at it appropriately for this type of group?&quot;.  <br><br>In the end- this is only a game, and well if death happens, that's why there are clerics :P<br><br><br><br> <p><IMG SRC="http://faeadari.homestead.com/files/sig.jpg" USEMAP="#sig" BORDER=0><MAP NAME="sig">  <AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="11,247,212,298" HREF="http://www.eqbloodsong.com"  ALT="Bloodsongs Homepage"  TARGET="_blank" >  <AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="223,208,423,278" HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=28361"  ALT="Faeadaris Profile"  TARGET="_blank">  <AREA SHAPE=RECT COORDS="90,142,281,203" HREF="http://eq.castersrealm.com/players/view_profile.asp?Id=43909"  ALT="Eylys profile"  TARGET="_blank" > </MAP></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3F3F3F><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/ucelitimberwolf.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Celi Timberwolf</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>BS Troublemaker. Oops!</span><br>  Posts: 121<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(5/16/01 9:09:07 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Phread's Barshin Fill-aw-su-fee</span><hr size=1> Good read Phread. I learned lots! There is one thing that I did not see in your post (may be there) which I think is worth mentioning. Tanks should not head out for the next pull half tanked. If you get a bad pull, the first thing the healer is going to do is heal you. And guess what. Everything jumps the healer. If the puller is completly healed, the group has time to think.<br><br>I was hunting in a group at the Mino cave in Steamfont when this happened. I was the healer and the tank came out of the cave with 5 minos. In this case, it probably did not matter how healed the tank was. I was going to get some. He was half healed to begin with and when he hit one bubble, I healed him and got three minos. I backed up and the three followed so it was time to visit the watchman. I did not get far because I was trying to message the group and keep from getting bonked.<br><br>Anyways, keeping the tank healthy is minor but does buy you time when things go bad. And your healers might live longer. <p>Celi Timberwolf<br>Officer/Web page MesserUpper<br>Master Fletcher, Tailor, Blacksmith, Brewer and<br>Grand Master Drunk</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#333333><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub20.ezboard.com/ubladecurser.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bladecurser</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Clarity PIMP</span><br>  Posts: 201<br> <font color=#6F6F6F>(9/7/01 5:49:06 am)</font><br>    <BR><img src=http://wsphotofews.excite.com/013/F2/Lb/ro/m326293.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Phread's Barshin Fill-aw-su-fee</span><hr size=1> Bumped <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm6.showPrevMessage?topicID=151.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm6.showNextMessage?topicID=151.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br></td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm6.emailToFriend?topicID=151.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm6.threadControl?topicID=151.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/grunge/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands (Moderator only)</a><br> <a href=http://pub20.ezboard.com/fbloodsongfrm6.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=151.topic>Subscribe</a> Click to receive email notifica